Bangladesh was all out for 110 in their first innings in the second and final Test against Sri Lanka at Mirpur. Today is the second day of the match. Mehidy Hasan Miraz remained 38 not out. Akila Dhananjaya bagged 3 for 20 while Suranga Lakmal had 3 for 25. The home team began the day on 56 for 4. Batting first, Sri Lanka made 222.